# Restart Dev Services After Code Changes

`dev.sh` and `npm run dev` run **without hot reload** for Python microservices. After editing code, restart the affected process so changes take effect.

## When to restart

| Changed paths | Restart |
|---------------|---------|
| `services/research/**` | Research service (port **8001**) |
| `services/scripting/**` | Scripting service (port **8002**) |
| `services/media/**` | Media service (port **8003**) |
| `services/seo/**` | SEO service (port **8004**) |
| `services/video-worker/**` | Celery worker |
| `frontend/**` | Next.js dev server (port **3030**) — usually auto-reloads; restart if behavior looks stale |

Do this **proactively** after implementing backend/frontend changes. Do not only tell the user to restart—run it yourself when you have shell access.

## Single-service restart (from repo root)

```bash
# Research (8001)
kill $(lsof -t -i:8001) 2>/dev/null
cd services && source venv/bin/activate && python -m uvicorn research.main:app --host 127.0.0.1 --port 8001 &

# Media (8003)
kill $(lsof -t -i:8003) 2>/dev/null
cd services && source venv/bin/activate && python -m uvicorn media.main:app --host 127.0.0.1 --port 8003 &
```

Swap `research` / port for `scripting` (8002), `media` (8003), or `seo` (8004).

## Full stack

```bash
./dev.sh start      # backend + celery + frontend (detached)
./dev.sh status     # verify all services
./dev.sh stop       # stop everything including frontend
```

App URL: **http://localhost:3030**

Research cold-starts can take **20–30 seconds** after `./dev.sh start`. Frontend first compile may take up to **~90 seconds**.

## Verify after restart

- Backend: `curl -s -o /dev/null -w "%{http_code}" http://127.0.0.1:8001/docs` → `200`
- New routes: hit the endpoint or check `/docs` on the service port
